HEADWORD: Delete
<hw>De*lete"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Deleted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Deleting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>deletus</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>delere</ets> to destroy. Cf. 1st <er>Dele</er>.]</ety> <def>To blot
out; to erase; to expunge; to dele; to omit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have, therefore, . . . inserted eleven stanzas which do not
appear in Sir Walter Scott's version, and have <qex>deleted</qex>
eight.</q> <rj><qau>Aytoun.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deleterious</ent>⟦br⟧
